channel.title: CVE Feed for Zyxel -- DX5401-B0 firmware
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Zyxel -- DX5401-B0 firmware

item.title: CVE-2023-28770|2023-05-10T00:00:00 -- zyxel -- dx5401-b0%20firmware
item.description: The sensitive information exposure vulnerability in the CGI “Export_Log” and the binary “zcmd” in Zyxel DX5401-B0 firmware versions prior to V5.17(ABYO.1)C0 could allow a remote unauthenticated attacker to read the system files and to retrieve the password of the supervisor from the encrypted file.

item.title: CVE-2023-28769|2023-04-27T00:00:00 -- zyxel -- dx5401-b0%20firmware
item.description: The buffer overflow vulnerability in the library “libclinkc.so” of the web server “zhttpd” in Zyxel DX5401-B0 firmware versions prior to V5.17(ABYO.1)C0 could allow a remote unauthenticated attacker to execute some OS commands or to cause denial-of-service (DoS) conditions on a vulnerable device.
